// DeepGrid Studio test level — map format v2 (plan2). Three stacked floors,
// 40×40 each. floors[0] is the lowest. The active area sits in the north-west
// corner (x 0..17, y 0..17); everything else is solid rock.
//
// Legend: '#'=Wall  '.'=Empty  '~'=Water  '^'=Fire  '%'=Poison  'H'=Ladder
//         '1'/'2'=Door kind 0/1   '<'=West '>'=East 'n'=North 'v'=South Horoscope
//
// The player starts on the MIDDLE floor (floor 1) at (4,4) facing East, looking
// across a pit that opens onto the room on floor 0 below (the "吹き抜け").
// Verification scenes (DEEPGRID_DEBUG_SHOT):
//   fall  : walk East off the ledge → drop into the floor-0 room.
//   ladder: turn South, walk to the ladder at (4,7), climb up to floor 2.
//   door  : turn West, open the kind-0 door directly ahead at (3,4).
// The map also contains a 2-floor drop (floor 2 → 0 at column (7,4)), a ladder
// that penetrates all three floors, a kind-1 door, a one-way Horoscope corridor,
// and a water/fire/poison pool for the liquid rendering.
(
    width: 40,
    height: 40,
    start_x: 4,
    start_y: 4,
    start_floor: 1,
    start_facing: East,
    floors: [
        // ---- floor 0 (bottom): a room under the pit + the ladder foot ----
